    "Id": "mechdef_fireball_ALM-S2",
    "Name": "Fireball",
    "Details": "Initially built to fight Elementals, the Fireball was made incredibly fast so that it could come to the aid of larger units. Unfortunately, this speed came at the cost of firepower leaving the 'Mech woefully underpowered to actually kill the Elementals it was supposed to defeat. Repurposed as a Scout and Raider, however, the mech served well with its ludicrously fast speed letting it outrun almost anything on the field. The Fireball is built around a massive five-ton DAV 220 extralight fusion engine, which propels the 'Mech to a cruising speed of 119 km/h and top speed of 184 km/h, allowing it to respond to a call from anywhere in the line for immediate support. The high speed of the Fireball comes at a price though, as the 'Mech only has four tons of armor protection and a very light weapons array. This upgraded version of the Fireball, debuting in 3076, uses an ER medium laser in each side torso, adds an ER small laser to the right arm, and enhances their accuracy through the use of a targeting computer. A MASC system boosts the 'Mech's maximum speed and heavy ferro-fibrous armor increases protection.<br><br>S-class mechs feature upgrades to their armour, thermal management and defensive systems that substantially improve their survivability on the 31st century battlefield.",
